    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently, Neovim only has `eol` option. `eol` can’t express CR and LF. Even if a text file doesn’t have end-of-file LF, it shows the `eol` character.\n\nRelated issue for Vim: https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/6981\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIn Unix-like systems which use LF as a new line,\n\n* if there is no LF in the end of the file, no eol character is shown.\n* listchars has an option to set the character for the hidden CR.",
